DataElement.preferredName: Qualitative Evaluation Survival Status Description Text java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A type of evaluation that is primarily descriptive and interpretative, and may or may not lend itself to quantification. Mainly concerned with the properties, the state, and the character (i.e., the nature) of phenomena. It implies an emphasis on processes and meanings that are rigorously examined, but not measured in terms of quantity, amount, or frequency. (www.unfpa.org/monitoring/toolkit/glossary.pdf and Nonprofit Good Practice Guide Glossary)_Continuance of life or existence especially under adverse conditions; includes methods and philosophy of survival.:A condition or state at a particular time.:A written or verbal account, representation, statement, or explanation of something.:The words of something written._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
